WEBVTT

00:01.634 --> 00:04.371
[cheerful music]

00:04.437 --> 00:12.379
♪ ♪

00:12.445 --> 00:14.681
♪ Harvey ♪

00:14.748 --> 00:16.416
♪ ♪

00:16.483 --> 00:18.752
♪ Harvey ♪

00:18.818 --> 00:24.424
♪ ♪

00:24.491 --> 00:26.326
♪ Harvey ♪

00:26.393 --> 00:30.196
♪ ♪

00:31.998 --> 00:34.134
Gather round, children.
Gather round.

00:34.200 --> 00:36.302
Yes, yes, even you, little one.

00:36.369 --> 00:39.072
For now that you are
six hours old,

00:39.139 --> 00:42.208
it is time for you
to hear your history.

00:42.275 --> 00:45.178
How did we come to live
in such a blessed land?

00:45.245 --> 00:49.182
Who rescued us
from certain annihilation?

00:49.249 --> 00:52.519
We know not
what he calls himself,

00:52.585 --> 00:54.988
but to me, he is

00:55.054 --> 00:58.124
The Great One.

00:58.191 --> 01:01.327
[mystical music]

01:01.394 --> 01:08.134
♪ ♪

01:08.201 --> 01:11.271
(Elder Bug)
Long ago, in our golden age,

01:11.337 --> 01:15.508
our people had just completed
our greatest achievement--

01:15.575 --> 01:17.377
The Sandy City.

01:17.444 --> 01:20.780
Our hearts were filled
with pride,

01:20.847 --> 01:22.348
and we rejoiced,

01:22.415 --> 01:26.119
ignorant of the destruction
that was coming...

01:26.186 --> 01:30.857
[laughing]

01:30.924 --> 01:34.260
(Elder Bug)
The Great Flood...

01:34.327 --> 01:35.962
[sniffs]

01:36.029 --> 01:37.197
Ah-choo!

01:37.263 --> 01:39.199
(Elder Bug)
The Great Storm...

01:39.265 --> 01:41.935
The Great Depression.

01:42.001 --> 01:43.736
[all screaming]

01:43.803 --> 01:46.739
{\an5}(Elder Bug)
At that moment,
I feared we were all doomed.

01:46.806 --> 01:50.410
[sniffs]
Hmm?

01:50.477 --> 01:54.314
Oh, snacks.

01:54.380 --> 01:56.049
- [cries]
- Calm down, little buglet.

01:56.115 --> 01:57.917
It's just a story.

01:57.984 --> 01:59.319
Now, where was I?
Ah, yes.

01:59.385 --> 02:02.722
I was thrown
into the creature's mouth.

02:02.789 --> 02:05.758
Hmm? Aah!

02:09.529 --> 02:11.965
Hey, you got
a little curly thing too,

02:12.031 --> 02:13.166
just like me.

02:13.233 --> 02:14.801
Boing, boing.

02:14.868 --> 02:18.271
Whoa, all of you have
the curly things.

02:18.338 --> 02:20.206
You're like a bunch
of little mes.

02:20.273 --> 02:21.875
(Elder Bug)
Having spared my life,

02:21.941 --> 02:26.346
I had one chance to reason
with the almighty being.

02:26.412 --> 02:27.480
[gasps]

02:27.547 --> 02:29.015
Did I do that?

02:29.082 --> 02:30.884
{\an1}I didn't realize
this is where you lived.

02:30.950 --> 02:32.619
Uh, it's okay.

02:32.685 --> 02:35.154
{\an1}I'll just put it back
the way it was.

02:35.221 --> 02:37.390
See, good as new.

02:37.457 --> 02:38.458
{\an1}[groans]

02:38.525 --> 02:40.627
{\an1}I'm so sorry
I broke your house.

02:40.693 --> 02:42.328
{\an1}I'll make sure you're safe
from now on.

02:42.395 --> 02:44.497
{\an1}I'll find you
a new place to live.

02:44.564 --> 02:48.635
{\an1}I just got to
figure out where.

02:48.701 --> 02:50.436
[Harvey groans]

02:50.503 --> 02:51.604
{\an3}Hey, Foo.

02:51.671 --> 02:55.275
{\an1}Shh, shh, shh.
Don't wake 'em up.

02:55.341 --> 02:57.677
No! Aah!
[screams]

02:57.744 --> 02:59.212
(Elder Bug)
It was yet another test

02:59.279 --> 03:03.516
for our people to endure--

03:03.583 --> 03:06.386
The Slappening.

03:07.654 --> 03:09.622
{\an3}Uh-uh.

03:09.689 --> 03:11.190
Ooh, don't.

03:11.257 --> 03:12.559
{\an3}You can't slap 'em,
Harvey.

03:12.625 --> 03:15.728
{\an1}What? There are bugs
in my bed, Foo!

03:15.795 --> 03:17.463
{\an3}They're not bugs.
They're my friends.

03:17.530 --> 03:20.400
{\an1}You're not friends with bugs.
You eat bugs.

03:20.466 --> 03:22.669
{\an3}I know,
but this is different.

03:22.735 --> 03:24.203
I smushed their house,

03:24.270 --> 03:26.773
{\an3}and they're gonna live here
with you in your house.

03:26.839 --> 03:27.974
{\an1}What? No.

03:28.041 --> 03:29.742
{\an1}Take 'em to live
in your tree.

03:29.809 --> 03:32.645
{\an3}They can't live in a tree.
They're too fancy.

03:32.712 --> 03:33.846
Look at 'em.

03:33.913 --> 03:35.782
{\an3}So fancy.

03:35.848 --> 03:39.018
{\an3}Harvey, I messed this up,
and I have to fix it.

03:39.085 --> 03:40.787
{\an3}I don't know
what else to do.

03:40.853 --> 03:42.255
{\an1}[groans]

03:42.322 --> 03:46.259
{\an1}This is really important
to you, huh?

03:46.326 --> 03:49.362
{\an1}All right. They're not gonna
stay in my room, though.

03:49.429 --> 03:51.564
{\an3}[gasps]
Yes!

03:51.631 --> 03:53.833
{\an1}Please just get that
away from me.

03:53.900 --> 03:56.302
{\an3}Yes!

03:56.369 --> 03:58.805
{\an1}Okay, they can stay
right here in this square.

03:58.871 --> 04:00.373
We'll call it bug zone.

04:00.440 --> 04:03.476
Okay, guys, stay.

04:03.543 --> 04:04.277
[gasps]

04:04.344 --> 04:06.279
Oh, no. Oh, no!

04:06.346 --> 04:08.014
No! No, no, no, no, no!

04:08.081 --> 04:09.916
{\an1}No, Foo!
I'm freaking out!

04:09.983 --> 04:12.418
{\an3}Yeah, they're not very good
with rules yet.

04:12.485 --> 04:15.221
{\an1}Tell you what, let's go
get them an aquarium,

04:15.288 --> 04:16.755
{\an1}and then you'll
go through the house

04:16.822 --> 04:19.425
and find every single one
of them and put 'em in it.

04:19.492 --> 04:21.027
Oh, that's a great idea.

04:21.094 --> 04:22.428
Let's go right now.

04:22.495 --> 04:24.697
Oh, they're probably
touching my clothes.

04:24.764 --> 04:26.899
(Elder Bug)
Little did we know

04:26.966 --> 04:29.702
our darkest time
was yet to come.

04:29.769 --> 04:33.840
Harvey, get ready for sardine
and cottage cheese sliders.

04:33.906 --> 04:37.176
[gasps]

04:38.311 --> 04:42.348
Aah! Aah! Aah!

04:44.083 --> 04:46.119
[screams]

04:46.185 --> 04:47.253
[telephone dialing]

04:47.320 --> 04:49.889
[doorbell rings]

04:49.956 --> 04:53.660
[whimpering]

04:53.726 --> 04:54.994
Well, hello, sir.

04:55.061 --> 04:56.229
I believe you called me.

04:56.295 --> 04:57.563
My name is Easy,

04:57.630 --> 05:00.233
{\an1}and I will be your exterminator
for the day.

05:00.299 --> 05:02.568
{\an1}Yep, those look like bugs,
all right.

05:02.635 --> 05:04.270
{\an3}I don't know
what I did wrong.

05:04.337 --> 05:06.406
{\an3}I try to keep a clean home,
darn it.

05:06.472 --> 05:08.341
{\an1}Hey, hey,
this isn't your fault.

05:08.408 --> 05:10.276
{\an1}Here, why don't you
do this?

05:10.343 --> 05:12.679
{\an1}Why don't you take some time,
walk around,

05:12.745 --> 05:14.147
look at some leaves?

05:14.213 --> 05:15.248
{\an1}And by the time
you get back,

05:15.314 --> 05:17.650
all the bugs
will be gone.

05:17.717 --> 05:19.852
{\an3}Okay. Okay,
that does sound good.

05:19.919 --> 05:23.122
{\an3}Uh, you're not gonna hurt any of
the little creatures, are you?

05:23.189 --> 05:26.325
{\an1}Oh, no. No, no, no.
Of course not.

05:26.392 --> 05:30.396
{\an1}We relocate the bugs
to a safe place far away

05:30.463 --> 05:33.499
{\an1}where they can roam free
and be happy

05:33.566 --> 05:36.169
{\an1}and live
happily ever after.

05:36.235 --> 05:37.837
Oh, wow. Okay.

05:37.904 --> 05:41.774
{\an1}All right, Mr. Easy,
I'll just leave you to it.

05:41.841 --> 05:44.977
Boy, I sure love lying.

05:47.647 --> 05:51.918
[light jazz music]
- [humming]

05:51.984 --> 06:00.760
♪ ♪

06:00.827 --> 06:02.862
[sniffing]

06:02.929 --> 06:04.597
(Elder Bug)
There is a saying, young ones,

06:04.664 --> 06:07.033
just as you think things
cannot get worse,

06:07.100 --> 06:08.234
they do.

06:08.301 --> 06:09.969
All right, you little freaks,

06:10.036 --> 06:11.370
time to die.

06:11.437 --> 06:12.805
Hi, friends.

06:12.872 --> 06:14.807
We have a new,
shiny house for you.

06:14.874 --> 06:15.908
{\an3}[gasps]

06:15.975 --> 06:19.445
[scatting]

06:19.512 --> 06:21.247
Who the heck is that guy?

06:21.314 --> 06:23.683
{\an3}We got to do something
before he hurts all my friends.

06:23.750 --> 06:25.251
{\an1}I know.
I'll talk to him.

06:25.318 --> 06:27.353
Um, excuse me, sir.

06:27.420 --> 06:29.288
My name is Harvey Beaks.

06:29.355 --> 06:31.257
{\an1}I'm a resident here,
and I was--

06:31.324 --> 06:33.226
{\an1}Oh, whoa!

06:33.292 --> 06:35.561
{\an1}Okay, that didn't go
as planned.

06:35.628 --> 06:39.732
{\an3}Don't worry.
I won't let him touch you.

06:39.799 --> 06:42.101
{\an3}There we go.
Thanks for the assist.

06:42.168 --> 06:45.404
[gasps]
No!

06:45.471 --> 06:48.074
{\an3}Hey!
That doesn't belong to you.

06:48.141 --> 06:49.542
Harvey, catch!

06:51.611 --> 06:52.812
Oh.

06:52.879 --> 06:54.347
{\an1}Oh. Oh, I get it.
We're playing a game now.

06:54.413 --> 06:55.815
That's cool.

06:55.882 --> 06:58.251
Aah! I'm not supposed to run
in the house!

06:58.317 --> 07:00.887
Go! Go, go, go.
Go, go, go.

07:00.953 --> 07:02.388
I'm sorry, guys.

07:02.455 --> 07:03.856
I'm not really good at this.

07:03.923 --> 07:07.059
{\an1}But I'm gonna protect you,
I swear.

07:10.596 --> 07:13.266
{\an1}That's right,
into the canister.

07:13.332 --> 07:16.669
{\an1}Every last one.
Come on!

07:16.736 --> 07:19.806
{\an3}No!

07:23.910 --> 07:25.878
And that's that.

07:25.945 --> 07:29.148
{\an5}(Elder Bug)
I wanted to believe
The Great One would save us,

07:29.215 --> 07:32.652
but it seemed too late.

07:32.718 --> 07:34.120
What do I do, Harvey?

07:34.187 --> 07:36.422
{\an1}I don't know if there's
anything to do.

07:36.489 --> 07:38.558
{\an1}The world's a dangerous
place for bugs.

07:38.624 --> 07:40.159
It's just how things work.

07:40.226 --> 07:42.028
No, it's not fair!

07:42.094 --> 07:43.696
Come on, Foo, think!

07:43.763 --> 07:47.200
And now to go home
and watch television.

07:47.266 --> 07:49.468
Hey!
What are you doing?

07:49.535 --> 07:52.672
{\an1}I'm gonna get you
out of there.

07:54.040 --> 07:56.475
(Elder Bug)
Our bodies were thrashed about

07:56.542 --> 07:58.644
in the intense cyclone.

07:58.711 --> 08:02.048
Would our suffering
never end?

08:04.050 --> 08:06.452
Oh, that's not good.

08:11.424 --> 08:13.292
I did it. It worked.

08:13.359 --> 08:14.694
You can't hurt them now.

08:14.760 --> 08:17.496
A vacuum is just a tool.

08:17.563 --> 08:20.166
I don't need tools
to get rid of bugs!

08:20.233 --> 08:21.300
{\an3}Aah!

08:21.367 --> 08:24.270
{\an1}No!

08:24.337 --> 08:26.672
Trust me.

08:28.808 --> 08:30.810
(Elder Bug)
My faith was tested.

08:30.877 --> 08:34.046
Was my destiny to be swallowed
by The Great One

08:34.113 --> 08:36.616
like a jelly bean?

08:36.682 --> 08:39.485
The Great One was not eating me.
He was saving me.

08:39.552 --> 08:42.955
He was protecting me
in his mouth.

08:43.022 --> 08:45.958
Oh, gross.

09:06.312 --> 09:08.915
[laughs]

09:08.981 --> 09:10.750
You got 'em all
in your mouth.

09:10.816 --> 09:14.120
That's so cool
and disgusting.

09:14.186 --> 09:15.788
Oh, there's one.

09:15.855 --> 09:19.725
{\an4}[muffled]
Harvey, you got to put the bug
in your mouth!

09:19.792 --> 09:21.928
What?
Ew! No way!

09:21.994 --> 09:23.930
{\an1}Now, don't do that,
little friend.

09:23.996 --> 09:27.233
{\an1}That bug deserves
what I'm about to do to him.

09:27.300 --> 09:30.603
{\an3}[groaning]

09:34.273 --> 09:37.610
{\an3}Oh, man.

09:40.079 --> 09:43.416
{\an6}[muffled]
You're not killing
any bugs today, Easy.

09:43.482 --> 09:46.385
Come on, Harvey.

09:46.452 --> 09:49.956
{\an3}Hey, uh,
how's it going in here?

09:50.022 --> 09:52.091
{\an1}Well, there's no more bugs
in the house.

09:52.158 --> 09:55.027
So here's my bill.

09:55.094 --> 09:56.896
$300?

09:56.963 --> 10:00.099
Really should have gotten
an estimate first.

10:03.536 --> 10:06.672
Thanks, Harvey.

10:06.739 --> 10:09.675
{\an1}That was the grossest thing
I've ever done.

10:09.742 --> 10:12.144
{\an1}But do you realize
what happened?

10:12.211 --> 10:13.145
{\an3}Nope.

10:13.212 --> 10:14.213
You did it, Foo.

10:14.280 --> 10:16.315
{\an1}You saved all your gross,
ugly bugs.

10:16.382 --> 10:17.416
I did?

10:17.483 --> 10:19.118
Oh, wow, I did!

10:19.185 --> 10:20.419
You guys, we made it!

10:20.486 --> 10:21.988
[laughs]

10:22.054 --> 10:24.657
I don't know what we're
gonna do with 'em now.

10:24.724 --> 10:27.226
Oh, yeah. Right.

10:27.293 --> 10:28.427
{\an3}[gasps]

10:28.494 --> 10:30.563
I got an idea.

10:30.629 --> 10:32.832
Can we put these
in your hair?

10:32.898 --> 10:33.632
{\an3}Yep.

10:33.699 --> 10:35.201
There you go, guys.

10:35.267 --> 10:36.736
It's perfect.

10:36.802 --> 10:38.738
{\an1}They don't have to worry
about getting wet or nothing,

10:38.804 --> 10:40.573
{\an1}because Fee
never takes a bath.

10:40.639 --> 10:42.308
Good idea, Foo.

10:42.375 --> 10:44.343
Oh, you know.

10:44.410 --> 10:47.079
And that is how The Great One
delivered us

10:47.146 --> 10:49.682
to the place
we now call home.

10:49.749 --> 10:51.384
But that was long ago,

10:51.450 --> 10:55.021
and I am now
nearly 6 days old.

10:55.087 --> 10:59.225
The sun sets for me
just as it rises for you.

10:59.291 --> 11:03.195
And now you must be the ones to
carry the tale of our salvation

11:03.262 --> 11:05.164
to the next generation.

11:05.231 --> 11:08.334
Children, I beg you,

11:08.401 --> 11:10.636
you must always remember

11:10.703 --> 11:12.805
The Great One.

11:12.872 --> 11:15.274
Ah-choo!
Ah.

11:20.613 --> 11:23.115
Hey, Harvey, big day today.

11:23.182 --> 11:25.951
The Old-Fashioned Days Festival
is always great--

11:26.018 --> 11:28.387
riding rides,
eating food on sticks,

11:28.454 --> 11:31.991
just you and me together,
like it is every year--

11:32.058 --> 11:34.860
our own special day.

11:34.927 --> 11:36.495
Oh, Harvey, you scamp.

11:36.562 --> 11:38.330
I can't tell you
what I'm gonna wear.

11:38.397 --> 11:41.600
You'll have to find out
when everybody else does.

11:41.667 --> 11:42.935
Get out of my room!

11:43.002 --> 11:45.004
Get out!
Get, get, get, get, get out!

11:45.071 --> 11:46.972
[breathing heavily]

11:47.039 --> 11:49.041
Oh, boy, oh, boy,
oh, boy, oh, boy,

11:49.108 --> 11:50.309
oh, boy, oh, boy, oh, boy.

11:50.376 --> 11:52.244
[doorbell rings]

11:52.311 --> 11:54.013
- Oh. Hey, Dade.
- Hey, buddy.

11:54.080 --> 11:56.782
{\an3}Are you ready to have
an old-fashioned dudes day?

11:56.849 --> 11:58.117
You know I am.

11:58.184 --> 11:58.918
{\an3}Aah.

11:58.984 --> 12:00.386
And guess what.

12:00.453 --> 12:02.955
{\an1}I invited Fee and Foo
to come with us this year.

12:03.022 --> 12:04.590
Isn't that great?

12:04.657 --> 12:06.492
(Fee)
Hey, barf butt.

12:06.559 --> 12:08.661
[object deflating]

12:08.727 --> 12:11.664
[upbeat music]

12:11.730 --> 12:18.471
♪ ♪

12:18.537 --> 12:21.240
Thanks again for inviting us
to the...

12:21.307 --> 12:23.042
Er, what's this thing
called again?

12:23.109 --> 12:25.144
The Old-Fashioned Days Festival.

12:25.211 --> 12:28.280
It's a yearly celebration
of our community's history

12:28.347 --> 12:32.151
{\an1}from way back when
everything was mystical--

12:32.218 --> 12:34.520
{\an1}the 1970s.

12:34.587 --> 12:37.156
{\an1}Oh, man, I'm so psyched
for you guys.

12:37.223 --> 12:39.058
{\an1}Remember the first time
we went, Dade?

12:39.125 --> 12:41.994
Yeah, back when it was
just the two of us.

12:42.061 --> 12:43.662
Psst, Harvey.

12:43.729 --> 12:44.730
Yeah, what's up, dude?

12:44.797 --> 12:46.332
{\an1}Um, okay,
how do I say this?

12:46.398 --> 12:49.101
{\an1}I just don't think Fee and Foo
get Old-Fashioned Days.

12:49.168 --> 12:50.369
What do you mean?

12:50.436 --> 12:52.037
{\an1}Well, just look
at Foo's costume.

12:52.104 --> 12:54.373
It's completely
inappropriate.

12:54.440 --> 12:55.407
{\an3}Hey, guys.

12:55.474 --> 12:57.076
What?
Everyone loves bananas.

12:57.143 --> 12:58.978
{\an1}But I thought
this was our day,

12:59.044 --> 13:00.813
our special day.

13:00.880 --> 13:02.448
It is special.

13:02.515 --> 13:05.417
{\an3}And now with Fee and Foo here,
it'll be even more special.

13:05.484 --> 13:07.620
{\an1}[groans]

13:07.686 --> 13:11.357
{\an5}(Harvey)
Here it is,
Old-Fashioned Days.

13:11.423 --> 13:14.226
So it's pretty crowded
in there.

13:14.293 --> 13:17.563
So we should abide
by the buddy system,

13:17.630 --> 13:19.064
you know, pair up and--

13:19.131 --> 13:21.667
- I call dibs on Harvey!
- I want to be your buddy too.

13:21.734 --> 13:23.669
Let's all be buddies!

13:23.736 --> 13:25.371
Hold hands, everybody.

13:25.437 --> 13:27.173
{\an1}(Dade)
Ick.

13:27.239 --> 13:28.574
{\an1}[groans]

13:28.641 --> 13:31.443
Do you guys feel that,
that warmth?

13:31.510 --> 13:33.112
{\an3}Yes.

13:33.179 --> 13:36.282
{\an1}Ugh, it's too warm.
Why is his hand so warm?

13:36.348 --> 13:38.250
That's our friendship.

13:38.317 --> 13:39.718
It's also my sweat.

13:39.785 --> 13:43.189
Okay, let's go!

13:44.123 --> 13:45.925
[bell dings, all gasp]

13:45.991 --> 13:47.927
(all)
Whoa!

13:47.993 --> 13:51.864
[funky disco music]

13:51.931 --> 13:56.535
Hey, you kids,
stay out of trouble.

13:56.602 --> 13:58.337
Uh, okay, weirdo.

13:58.404 --> 14:00.673
Guys,
let's go there first!

14:00.739 --> 14:03.943
♪ ♪

14:04.009 --> 14:06.412
Harvey! Harvey!
I lost you, buddy.

14:06.478 --> 14:07.513
Where are you?

14:07.580 --> 14:08.514
{\an3}[roars]

14:08.581 --> 14:10.683
Harvey! Harvey!
Save me, Harvey!

14:10.749 --> 14:12.484
[all screaming and laughing]

14:12.551 --> 14:14.853
Whoa! Oh, whoa!

14:14.920 --> 14:16.822
{\an1}Oh, cool,
scratch 'n sniff.

14:16.889 --> 14:18.123
Here you go, guys.

14:18.190 --> 14:20.793
[all sniffing]

14:20.859 --> 14:23.762
{\an1}I got cleaning supplies!
My favorite!

14:23.829 --> 14:25.164
Buttered corn on the cob!

14:25.231 --> 14:27.299
Newly washed baby!

14:27.366 --> 14:28.601
[coughs]

14:28.667 --> 14:30.336
Old-man butt!

14:30.402 --> 14:32.338
Whoa, lucky.

14:32.404 --> 14:33.839
{\an3}[groans]

14:33.906 --> 14:37.843
I don't remember them having
a rock petting zoo last year.

14:37.910 --> 14:39.645
- Cool.
- Harvey!

14:39.712 --> 14:42.414
Look what I got for us.

14:42.481 --> 14:43.682
Oh, fiddlesticks.

14:43.749 --> 14:45.451
There's only two spoons.

14:45.517 --> 14:47.820
{\an1}I guess that means
only the two of us can--

14:47.886 --> 14:49.288
{\an1}Hey!

14:49.355 --> 14:51.257
{\an3}[chomps]
Thanks, Dade.

14:51.323 --> 14:52.291
{\an1}[groans]

14:52.358 --> 14:53.659
What's next, Harvey?

14:53.726 --> 14:56.262
Well, how about we--

14:56.328 --> 14:58.864
Oh, my gosh!
Sweet Baby Hannah!

14:58.931 --> 15:00.866
That's the only Buddy Baby

15:00.933 --> 15:02.835
from this year's collection
I don't have!

15:02.901 --> 15:04.870
Let me win that
for you, Harvey!

15:04.937 --> 15:07.573
Let me win that for you!

15:07.640 --> 15:09.141
[grunts]

15:09.208 --> 15:12.678
No, don't worry, Harvey.
I got this.

15:12.745 --> 15:14.613
[grunts]

15:14.680 --> 15:18.083
[grunting]

15:19.518 --> 15:21.987
{\an1}It's okay, Dade.
I don't really need it.

15:22.054 --> 15:25.557
Hey, Harvey, want to see
something funny?

15:25.624 --> 15:28.994
Yes, please.

15:29.061 --> 15:31.263
{\an3}Looks like we've got
a winner!

15:31.330 --> 15:32.264
{\an1}What?

15:32.331 --> 15:33.265
{\an1}Whoa!

15:33.332 --> 15:35.534
Dade, Fee and Foo won it!

15:35.601 --> 15:36.702
Did you see?

15:36.769 --> 15:38.404
That's it.

15:38.470 --> 15:42.441
I'm gonna make special memories
with Harvey if it kills me.

15:42.508 --> 15:44.476
Those good-for-nothing twins
have got to go.

15:44.543 --> 15:47.346
But how?
Poison? Giant bees?

15:47.413 --> 15:49.615
More poison?
Poison bees?

15:49.682 --> 15:50.983
All right, listen up.

15:51.050 --> 15:53.152
{\an1}There's something wrong
with the disco ball ride.

15:53.218 --> 15:55.154
{\an1}You can't let anybody
touch the controls,

15:55.220 --> 15:57.723
or else it may go haywire
and blow up or something.

15:57.790 --> 16:01.360
{\an1}So, to reiterate, if somebody,
like, oh, I don't know,

16:01.427 --> 16:03.395
a couple of wild
and crazy kids,

16:03.462 --> 16:05.731
{\an1}if they were to mess
with the controls of that ride,

16:05.798 --> 16:08.300
they would get kicked out,
and whoever they were with

16:08.367 --> 16:11.136
{\an1}would have to spend the rest
of their day without them.

16:11.203 --> 16:13.872
{\an6}[gasps]
Oh, my gosh,
I love you guys!

16:13.939 --> 16:15.607
- [laughs]
- What?

16:15.674 --> 16:17.843
Harvey, look at what
I found in the trash.

16:17.910 --> 16:21.280
Guys, let's go on that ride,
all four of us, right now.

16:21.347 --> 16:23.816
[disco music]

16:23.882 --> 16:27.619
[Fee and Foo screaming]

16:30.022 --> 16:31.757
Okay, yelling contest over.

16:31.824 --> 16:33.425
Dade, who won?

16:33.492 --> 16:36.195
Listen, I didn't want to be
the one to tell you this,

16:36.261 --> 16:38.497
but you see that thing
over there?

16:38.564 --> 16:40.165
{\an3}(Fee)
What, like, that box thing?

16:40.232 --> 16:43.802
Yeah. Um, it's alive,
and it talks.

16:43.869 --> 16:46.372
And I heard it say
some mean stuff about you.

16:46.438 --> 16:48.707
{\an1}That's so like a box
to be like that.

16:48.774 --> 16:50.175
Well, what did it say?

16:50.242 --> 16:54.380
Uh, it said that
you and Foo are wack.

16:54.446 --> 16:57.082
{\an3}Ugh, I hate when people
call me that.

16:57.149 --> 16:58.550
Come on, Foo.

16:58.617 --> 17:00.886
[grunting]

17:00.953 --> 17:03.355
Uh, what are you guys doing?

17:03.422 --> 17:05.656
{\an3}I'll show you
who's wack!

17:05.723 --> 17:06.692
[bell dings]

17:06.759 --> 17:09.694
[disco music]

17:09.762 --> 17:14.967
♪ ♪

17:15.032 --> 17:17.703
[screaming]

17:17.770 --> 17:19.204
Oh, my goodness!

17:19.271 --> 17:22.040
Hi, Mr. Officer Fred.

17:22.107 --> 17:24.209
{\an1}Ba-zap!

17:24.276 --> 17:26.377
{\an3}Fee! Foo!

17:26.444 --> 17:28.647
{\an1}Harvey, Harvey,
Harvey, Harvey, Harvey.

17:28.714 --> 17:30.215
The twins are fine.

17:30.282 --> 17:32.017
{\an1}Listen, I'm just
as surprised as you are.

17:32.084 --> 17:34.887
{\an1}But, you know, they would
want you to keep having fun.

17:34.953 --> 17:37.756
{\an1}They wouldn't want something
terrible that they did

17:37.823 --> 17:40.125
to ruin our day together.

17:40.192 --> 17:42.161
I guess that makes sense.

17:42.227 --> 17:43.562
{\an1}Great!
It's settled, then.

17:43.629 --> 17:44.630
{\an1}[laughs]

17:44.696 --> 17:46.331
Sweet molasses!

17:46.398 --> 17:48.200
We could hippety-hop
on that Afro Bounce.

17:48.267 --> 17:50.469
{\an3}Sweet blazes, this is gonna be
a beautiful day.

17:50.536 --> 17:54.473
{\an3}Oh, gosh, Harvey, look!
A photo booth.

17:55.841 --> 17:59.278
{\an1}All right! Let's see
how they came out.

18:02.748 --> 18:05.484
{\an1}I-I don't get it.
Why are you so bummed?

18:05.551 --> 18:07.553
{\an3}I guess I just miss
Fee and Foo.

18:07.619 --> 18:09.388
{\an3}I feel bad
they got kicked out.

18:09.455 --> 18:12.357
{\an4}[sighs]
Why do you care so much
about those two?

18:12.424 --> 18:14.760
{\an1}They're stinky, and they're
gross and stinky.

18:14.827 --> 18:17.863
{\an3}They're my friends, dude.
They're fun to hang out with.

18:17.930 --> 18:21.033
What? I-I just--

18:21.099 --> 18:23.202
What--what about me?

18:23.268 --> 18:25.704
{\an1}I mean, aren't I fun
to hang out with?

18:25.771 --> 18:27.406
Dude, of course.

18:27.473 --> 18:28.740
You're my friend.

18:28.807 --> 18:30.309
We have tons of fun,

18:30.375 --> 18:31.910
{\an3}but don't you think
it's kind of hard to have fun

18:31.977 --> 18:33.745
{\an3}when your friends
are feeling bummed?

18:33.812 --> 18:35.614
Oh. Yeah.

18:35.681 --> 18:37.216
That's--that's true.

18:37.282 --> 18:40.385
{\an3}I just wish we could all
have fun together.

18:44.823 --> 18:47.326
{\an1}Aah! I'm gonna
make this right, Harvey.

18:47.392 --> 18:48.660
Just give me a sec.

18:48.727 --> 18:49.928
{\an3}Okay.

18:49.995 --> 18:51.196
Don't worry, Harvey.

18:51.263 --> 18:52.431
I'll turn that frown
upside down.

18:52.498 --> 18:53.765
{\an3}Officer Fred, could you
please maybe

18:53.832 --> 18:55.400
{\an3}let Fee and Foo
into the park maybe?

18:55.467 --> 18:57.135
- No.
- Okay, yes. Right.

18:57.202 --> 18:59.404
{\an3}So sorry, Officer. I would
never question your authority.

18:59.471 --> 19:01.406
Got to get Fee and Foo
back into the park...

19:01.473 --> 19:03.041
for Harvey.

19:03.108 --> 19:06.378
{\an1}You hit the other side
yet, Foo?

19:06.445 --> 19:08.480
No, but I ate five worms.

19:08.547 --> 19:10.449
{\an3}Psst.
Fee, Foo, over here.

19:10.516 --> 19:12.017
What are you doing here?

19:12.084 --> 19:14.386
{\an1}Shouldn't you and Harvey be
having fun together right now?

19:14.453 --> 19:16.488
Uh, yeah, you'd think so.

19:16.555 --> 19:18.624
{\an3}Look, you guys want to
bust back in, right?

19:18.690 --> 19:19.892
{\an1}Uh, doy!

19:19.958 --> 19:22.661
What does it look
like we're doing?

19:22.728 --> 19:25.531
{\an3}I don't--I don't really know,
to be honest.

19:25.597 --> 19:27.533
(man)
All right, almost showtime.

19:27.599 --> 19:29.501
We got to get
this gear loaded.

19:29.568 --> 19:33.705
Okay, I think
I have a plan.

19:33.772 --> 19:34.773
{\an1}[grunts]

19:34.840 --> 19:35.741
{\an1}Oh, jeez.

19:35.807 --> 19:37.643
{\an1}Was this thing
so heavy before?

19:37.709 --> 19:40.312
{\an1}Hey, man, thanks
for helping us get back in.

19:40.379 --> 19:42.047
{\an1}That's pretty awesome
of you.

19:42.114 --> 19:43.515
You're groovy, Dade.

19:43.582 --> 19:45.951
{\an3}[groans]
No, I'm not groovy.

19:46.018 --> 19:48.787
{\an3}I-I've been trying to get rid
of you guys all day.

19:48.854 --> 19:50.622
I wanted Harvey
all to myself--

19:50.689 --> 19:52.858
{\an3}just us two,
like we used to be.

19:52.925 --> 19:53.959
{\an3}I'm sorry.

19:54.026 --> 19:55.494
Eh, that's okay, man.

19:55.561 --> 19:57.262
{\an1}Let's figure out how
to get back at Officer Fred

19:57.329 --> 19:58.597
for kicking us out.

19:58.664 --> 20:01.400
{\an3}Uh, yeah.
Well, I'm actually the one

20:01.466 --> 20:04.770
{\an3}that got you kicked out
by Officer Fred.

20:04.836 --> 20:06.305
{\an1}You what?

20:06.371 --> 20:10.208
{\an3}(Dade)
Aah! No, not my face!

20:10.275 --> 20:13.211
[mellow music]

20:13.278 --> 20:18.951
♪ ♪

20:19.017 --> 20:22.521
{\an3}♪ Let me apologize,
let me explain ♪

20:22.588 --> 20:26.725
{\an3}♪ 'Cause I'm so sorry
for everything ♪

20:26.792 --> 20:29.895
♪ I wanted Harvey
to be my friend ♪

20:29.962 --> 20:31.730
{\an3}♪ But with you two
in the way ♪

20:31.797 --> 20:33.665
{\an3}♪ It seemed our friendship
might end ♪

20:33.732 --> 20:37.769
{\an1}♪ Well, you're a doofus
for thinking that was the case ♪

20:37.836 --> 20:41.740
{\an1}♪ You really deserve
another punch in the face ♪

20:41.807 --> 20:42.908
{\an3}Aah!

20:42.975 --> 20:45.410
{\an3}♪ But now I know
that I was wrong ♪

20:45.477 --> 20:49.748
{\an3}♪ And I was really hoping
we could get along ♪

20:49.815 --> 20:53.619
{\an3}♪ It hurt Harvey
when I tried to hurt you ♪

20:53.685 --> 20:55.554
(both)
♪ So, for our buddy ♪

20:55.621 --> 20:58.223
♪ I'll be your buddy too ♪

20:58.290 --> 20:59.891
♪ Ah-ah-ah, ah-ah-ah ♪

20:59.958 --> 21:01.360
{\an3}♪ Ahh! ♪

21:01.426 --> 21:03.528
(all)
♪ We all love Harvey ♪

21:03.595 --> 21:05.497
♪ And 'cause we do ♪

21:05.564 --> 21:10.268
♪ I'll try to tolerate you ♪

21:10.335 --> 21:12.404
♪ Yeah, we all love Harvey ♪

21:12.471 --> 21:15.207
♪ And that's the truth ♪

21:15.273 --> 21:19.111
♪ And so I'll put up with you ♪

21:19.177 --> 21:22.147
[cheers and applause]

21:23.915 --> 21:26.652
{\an3}Guys, I heard music
when I was in the bathroom.

21:26.718 --> 21:28.086
How'd you sneak back in?

21:28.153 --> 21:29.521
{\an3}Uh, well...

21:29.588 --> 21:30.922
It was Dade's idea.

21:30.989 --> 21:32.457
{\an1}He's pretty smart
for a whiny tattletale.

21:32.524 --> 21:33.925
{\an3}Thanks.

21:33.992 --> 21:36.628
{\an3}I'm so glad to have my friends
back together.

21:36.695 --> 21:38.997
It's all I ever wanted.

21:39.064 --> 21:41.066
{\an3}Lawbreakers!
Uh-huh, I see you up there!

21:41.133 --> 21:43.935
By sneaking back in here,
you're in violation

21:44.002 --> 21:45.003
of festival law!

21:45.070 --> 21:47.239
Run!

21:47.305 --> 21:50.208
[cheers and laughter]

21:50.275 --> 21:52.210
{\an1}[laughs]

21:52.277 --> 21:54.246
[laughter]

21:54.312 --> 21:57.149
{\an3}(Officer Fred)
Ba-zap!
